File: A SARS office. JOHANNESBURG - In an effort to fight financial crime, SARS has partnered with its US counterpart -- the IRS -- and its criminal investigation division. READ: SARS eyes offshore wealth The two will work together to investigate crimes such as international public corruption, cyber fraud and money laundering, among others. SARS Commissioner Edward Kieswetter says the partnership is in line with the revenue service's renewed focus on non-compliant, high-wealth individuals and offshore holdings.